content:
I've seen many friends say that contributors hope for a "wise ruler"
I actually think there's nothing wrong with hoping for a "wise ruler" now, and it's very likely that China now has only one way to be saved, which is to rely on a "wise ruler".
As for why? You can't expect the people to realize that they should fight for their rights, but it's more likely that Xi Jinping will suddenly convert to Buddhism and put down his butcher knife.
After all, he also said that there is a god above you, so there's a possibility that he believes in Buddhism.
